# Eventio 3.0 Overview

College event platform for Somaiya University. Council creates events; faculty/principal approve; students register and attend.

## Active workspaces (only these four)

| Path | Role | Stack |
|------|------|-------|
| `backend/` | REST API, auth, Prisma, business logic | Express, port **8000** |
| `frontend/app/` | **Student** portal — browse, register, my events | Next.js App Router |
| `frontend/council-app/` | **Council** portal — create events, approvals, controls | Next.js App Router |
| `frontend/faculty/` | **Faculty / Principal** portal — review, approve, return | Next.js App Router |

## Ignore completely (redundant dead code)

**Never** read, search, edit, copy from, or suggest changes in:

- `frontend/student/`
- `frontend/council/`
- `frontend/dean/`

These are obsolete Vite SPAs superseded by `frontend/app/`, `frontend/council-app/`, and `frontend/faculty/`. Treat them as if they do not exist. Do not use them as reference when implementing features — use the active Next.js apps instead.

## Auth & roles

- Google OAuth only (`somaiya.edu` in production)
- Roles: `USER`, `COUNCIL`, `FACULTY`, `PRINCIPAL`, `ADMIN`
- API prefix: `/api/v1`

## Key backend files

- `backend/prisma/schema.prisma` — data models & enums
- `backend/routes/event.route.js` — events, registration, attendance, state updates
- `backend/middleware/auth.middleware.js` — JWT
- `backend/middleware/field-validator.middlware.js` — role-based field allowlist on event updates

## Conventions

- Minimize diff scope; match existing patterns in the touched app
- Do not commit unless explicitly asked
- State machine lives in Prisma `STATE` enum — see `event-lifecycle` rule
